This paper deals with optimization problems related to graphs, specifically the robust mincut and shortest path problems. The techniques used involve approximation algorithms and analysis, which are common in the sub-categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
